### The calorimeter

For reactions involving solutions, a simple calorimeter consisting of a polystyrene cup with a lid and a thermometer can be used to measure the heat change.

The temperature changes are relatively small, so for accurate work the thermometer should have a precision of \(\pm 0.1^{\circ}\)C.

