The term, [-TAS] in the equation \(\Delta G=\Delta H-TAS\) indicates that \(\Delta G\) is temperature-dependent. However, we can assume that \(\Delta H\) and \(\Delta S\) remain roughly constant regardless of temperature and use them to calculate \(\Delta G\) at other temperatures.

